{
    "id": "electronics/voltage-divider",
    "title": "Build a Voltage Divider",
    "description": "Split 5 V to about 2.5 V using 220 \u03a9 and 10 k\u03a9 resistors on a Breadboard.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/basic_circuit.svg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Orion here. Gather a Breadboard, 220 \u03a9 resistor, 10 k\u03a9 resistor, two Jumper Wires, a 5 V Power Supply and a digital multimeter. Keep the supply unplugged while wiring.",
            "options": [{ "type": "goto", "goto": "build", "text": "I'm ready" }]
        },
        {
            "id": "build",
            "text": "Place the 220 \u03a9 and 10 k\u03a9 resistors in series on the Breadboard. Use two Jumper Wires to connect the 5 V Power Supply across them and clip the multimeter probes to the junction. Double-check resistor color bands before powering.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "verify-resistor-color-code",
                    "text": "Check resistor colors"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "measure",
                    "text": "Resistors placed",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        { "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f", "count": 1 },
                        { "id": "037e6065-68a7-4ad1-9b0b-7778ecfe0662", "count": 1 },
                        { "id": "ffe0b74a-f111-4d66-b4c3-d82965a976ac", "count": 1 },
                        { "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066", "count": 2 },
                        { "id": "828d6c3b-66a5-4064-b221-97630274502b", "count": 1 },
                        { "id": "5127e156-3009-4db4-85ac-e3ea070b68f2", "count": 1 }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "measure",
            "text": "Plug in the 5 V Power Supply and measure the junction. It should read about 2.5 V on the multimeter; stop if the reading jumps or parts heat up.",
            "options": [{ "type": "goto", "goto": "finish", "text": "Measured ~2.5 V" }]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Nice work! That's how a voltage divider sets a lower reference voltage.",
